cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.NA. 

The paper presents algorithms for maintaining a topological order of a directed acyclic graph and detecting cycles as arcs are added, which are fundamental problems in graph theory and algorithms. The paper also extends the algorithms to the maintenance of strong components. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves combinatorial geometry and analysis of algorithms, which suggest possible categories of cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also discusses the performance of the algorithms, which may involve numerical analysis and optimization, leading to possible categories of cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
